    <section class="section">
        <div class="container spec-sheet-container">
            <div class="breadcrumb">
                <a asp-page="/Products">‹ Back to Products</a>
            </div>

            <div class="spec-sheet-main">
                <div class="spec-sheet-content">
                    <h2>Custom-Built for Quality Control</h2>
                    <p>This Lab Coating Gauge is a quality control instrument designed for offline product sampling. While RSI's online gauges automate coating thickness control during production, this lab gauge is used to verify the final quality. It checks random samples from the finished coil, providing critical statistical data on the final coating weight. The laboratory coating weight gauge is designed to allow samples to be checked simply and easily with no adjustments necessary by the user, thus providing an unambiguous and reliable measurement of coating weight by unskilled operators. For more information on our custom-build process, see our <a asp-page="/Solutions">Solutions page</a>.</p>
                    
                    <h3>Key Features & Specifications</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Application:</strong> Offline laboratory gauge for final product quality control.</li>
                        <li><strong>Coating Types Measured:</strong> Zinc, Galvanneal, Aluminum Type 1 & 2, and ZAM® (Zn-Al-Mg).</li>
                        <li><strong>Substrates Measured:</strong> Carbon Steel and 409 Stainless Steel.</li>
                         <li><strong>Substrate Thickness:</strong> 0.35 to 3.5 Millimeters.</li>
                        <li><strong>Hardware:</strong> Features a Bench Top Head Enclosure with an air-cooled X-ray measuring head and foot switch for raising and lowering the sample clamp.</li>
                        <li><strong>Operator Interface:</strong> Includes a 17" Operator's Display for grade code entry, measurement display, and tolerance limit indicators.</li>
                        <li><strong>Operating System:</strong> Utilizes Ubuntu (Linux) Real-Time Operating System for robust and reliable performance.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
